_components.description: Making good choices makes us a good citizen.
You can make good choices on what to do when you get angry.

Some people start yelling when they get angry.
Anger can make us want to strike out.
Seeing the signs of anger lets you make better choices.
When you're angry, one good choice can be walking away.
Counting to ten can help you control your anger.
A good, deep breath can help clear your head.
It's easier to make good choices when you're calm.
Every day we face frustrations.
Using your mind is a lot better than an anger take over.
Anger can cause you to make bad choices.
We are always responsible for our choices√ëgood and bad!
When your anger makes choices for you, you visit the office.
It's important to manage your anger.
If you pay attention, it is easier to make good choices.
Managing your anger is an important part of sportsmanship.
Disappointment is one of many things that can lead to anger.
Bossy people are all around us.
If we let it, anger can make us act out of control.
Being so angry you blow up is no fun!
Sometimes when you are very worried it comes out as angry.
No matter how angry you are, it's never okay to hit.
